                  <persName id="t18300916-304-person2498">
                  JAMES 
                  WATSON
               <interp inst="t18300916-304-person2498" type="surname" value="WATSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-304-person2498" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-304-person2498" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in <placeName id="t18300916-304-crimeloc1556">Leonard-square, Shoreditch</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-304-crimeloc1556" type="placeName" value="Leonard-square, Shoreditch"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-304-crimeloc1556" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-304-off1554 t18300916-304-crimeloc1556"></join>, and am a <rs id="t18300916-304-viclabel1557" type="occupation">broker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-304-victim2497 t18300916-304-viclabel1557"></join>. These brushes hung on a nail about five feet from the ground - they were on the door-post, but inside the shop; I was sitting at tea about five o'clock, in the parlour adjoining the shop, and saw the prisoner pass in a very suspicious way - I ran out, and saw him about ten yards off, with something concealed under his coat; he was turning down Leonard-street - I followed, and saw him turn and look behind him; I got before him, and he dropped the brushes from under his coat - he ran away, and I after him; he was stopped almost directly - I returned, and picked up the brushes; I am sure they are mine - I had seen them safe an hour and a half before; I have an ink mark on them - I observed two very suspicious characters on the other side of the way at the time.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Will you swear you had seen them within three hours? A. I will not swear to the time - I put an ink mark on them afterwards - they are common brushes; I only had four of that kind - I can swear to them without the ink mark, but was persuaded by the serjeant of Police to ink them, to know they were what I gave him - I swear positively to them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-304-person2499">
